97// This is the global static registry of scripts.
98template<class TScript>
99class ScriptRegistry
100{
101 public:
102
103 typedef std::map<uint32, TScript*> ScriptMap;
104 typedef typename ScriptMap::iterator ScriptMapIterator;
105
106 // The actual list of scripts. This will be accessed concurrently, so it must not be modified
107 // after server startup.
108 static ScriptMap ScriptPointerList;
109 static std::vector<TScript*> Scripts;
110
111 static void AddScript(TScript* const script, bool addToDeleteContainer = true)
112 {
113 ASSERT(script);
114
115 // See if the script is using the same memory as another script. If this happens, it means that
116 // someone forgot to allocate new memory for a script.
117 for (ScriptMapIterator it = ScriptPointerList.begin(); it != ScriptPointerList.end(); ++it)
118 {
119 if (it->second == script)
120 {
121 TC_LOG_ERROR("scripts", "Script '%s' has same memory pointer as '%s'.",
122 script->GetName().c_str(), it->second->GetName().c_str());
123
124 return;
125 }
126 }
127
128 AddScript(is_script_database_bound<TScript>{}, script);
129 if (addToDeleteContainer)
130 Scripts.push_back(script);
131 }
132
133 // Gets a script by its ID (assigned by ObjectMgr).
134 static TScript* GetScriptById(uint32 id)
135 {
136 ScriptMapIterator it = ScriptPointerList.find(id);
137 if (it != ScriptPointerList.end())
138 return it->second;
139
140 return NULL;
141 }
142
143 private:
144
145 // Adds a database bound script
146 static void AddScript(std::true_type, TScript* const script)
147 {
148 // Get an ID for the script. An ID only exists if it's a script that is assigned in the database
149 // through a script name (or similar).
150 uint32 id = sObjectMgr->GetScriptId(script->GetName());
151 if (id)
152 {
153 // Try to find an existing script.
154 bool existing = false;
155 for (ScriptMapIterator it = ScriptPointerList.begin(); it != ScriptPointerList.end(); ++it)
156 {
157 // If the script names match...
158 if (it->second->GetName() == script->GetName())
159 {
160 // ... It exists.
161 existing = true;
162 break;
163 }
164 }
165
166 // If the script isn't assigned -> assign it!
167 if (!existing)
168 {
169 ScriptPointerList[id] = script;
170 sScriptMgr->IncrementScriptCount();
171
172 #ifdef SCRIPTS
173 UnusedScriptNamesContainer::iterator itr = std::lower_bound(UnusedScriptNames.begin(), UnusedScriptNames.end(), script->GetName());
174 if (itr != UnusedScriptNames.end() && *itr == script->GetName())
175 UnusedScriptNames.erase(itr);
176 #endif
177 }
178 else
179 {
180 // If the script is already assigned -> delete it!
181 TC_LOG_ERROR("scripts", "Script '%s' already assigned with the same script name, so the script can't work.",
182 script->GetName().c_str());
183
184 ABORT(); // Error that should be fixed ASAP.
185 }
186 }
187 else
188 {
189 // The script uses a script name from database, but isn't assigned to anything.
190 TC_LOG_ERROR("sql.sql", "Script named '%s' does not have a script name assigned in database.", script->GetName().c_str());
191 }
192 }
193
194 // Adds a non database bound script
195 static void AddScript(std::false_type, TScript* const script)
196 {
197 // We're dealing with a code-only script; just add it.
198 ScriptPointerList[_scriptIdCounter++] = script;
199 sScriptMgr->IncrementScriptCount();
200 }
201
202 // Counter used for code-only scripts.
203 static uint32 _scriptIdCounter;
204};
205
206// Utility macros to refer to the script registry.
207#define SCR_REG_MAP(T) ScriptRegistry<T>::ScriptMap
208#define SCR_REG_ITR(T) ScriptRegistry<T>::ScriptMapIterator
209#define SCR_REG_LST(T) ScriptRegistry<T>::ScriptPointerList
210#define SCR_REG_VEC(T) ScriptRegistry<T>::Scripts
211
212// Utility macros for looping over scripts.
213#define FOR_SCRIPTS(T, C, E) \
214 if (SCR_REG_LST(T).empty()) \
215 return; \
216 for (SCR_REG_ITR(T) C = SCR_REG_LST(T).begin(); \
217 C != SCR_REG_LST(T).end(); ++C)
218#define FOR_SCRIPTS_RET(T, C, E, R) \
219 if (SCR_REG_LST(T).empty()) \
220 return R; \
221 for (SCR_REG_ITR(T) C = SCR_REG_LST(T).begin(); \
222 C != SCR_REG_LST(T).end(); ++C)
223#define FOREACH_SCRIPT(T) \
224 FOR_SCRIPTS(T, itr, end) \
225 itr->second
226
227// Utility macros for finding specific scripts.
228#define GET_SCRIPT(T, I, V) \
229 T* V = ScriptRegistry<T>::GetScriptById(I); \
230 if (!V) \
231 return;
232#define GET_SCRIPT_RET(T, I, V, R) \
233 T* V = ScriptRegistry<T>::GetScriptById(I); \
234 if (!V) \
235 return R;

249void ScriptMgr::Initialize()
250{
251 uint32 oldMSTime = getMSTime();
252
253 LoadDatabase();
254
255 TC_LOG_INFO("server.loading", "Loading C++ scripts");
256
257 FillSpellSummary();
258 AddScripts();
259
260#ifdef SCRIPTS
261 for (std::string const& scriptName : UnusedScriptNames)
262 {
263 TC_LOG_ERROR("sql.sql", "ScriptName '%s' exists in database, but no core script found!", scriptName.c_str());
264 }
265#endif
266
267 TC_LOG_INFO("server.loading", ">> Loaded %u C++ scripts in %u ms", GetScriptCount(), GetMSTimeDiffToNow(oldMSTime));
268}

270void ScriptMgr::Unload()
271{
272 #define SCR_CLEAR(T) \
273 for (T* scr : SCR_REG_VEC(T)) \
274 delete scr; \
275 SCR_REG_VEC(T).clear();
276
277 // Clear scripts for every script type.
278 SCR_CLEAR(SpellScriptLoader);
279 SCR_CLEAR(ServerScript);
280 SCR_CLEAR(WorldScript);
281 SCR_CLEAR(FormulaScript);
282 SCR_CLEAR(WorldMapScript);
283 SCR_CLEAR(InstanceMapScript);
284 SCR_CLEAR(BattlegroundMapScript);
285 SCR_CLEAR(ItemScript);
286 SCR_CLEAR(CreatureScript);
287 SCR_CLEAR(GameObjectScript);
288 SCR_CLEAR(AreaTriggerScript);
289 SCR_CLEAR(BattlegroundScript);
290 SCR_CLEAR(OutdoorPvPScript);
291 SCR_CLEAR(CommandScript);
292 SCR_CLEAR(WeatherScript);
293 SCR_CLEAR(AuctionHouseScript);
294 SCR_CLEAR(ConditionScript);
295 SCR_CLEAR(VehicleScript);
296 SCR_CLEAR(DynamicObjectScript);
297 SCR_CLEAR(TransportScript);
298 SCR_CLEAR(AchievementCriteriaScript);
299 SCR_CLEAR(PlayerScript);
300 SCR_CLEAR(AccountScript);
301 SCR_CLEAR(GuildScript);
302 SCR_CLEAR(GroupScript);
303 SCR_CLEAR(UnitScript);
304
305 #undef SCR_CLEAR
306
307 delete[] SpellSummary;
308 delete[] UnitAI::AISpellInfo;
309}

316void ScriptMgr::FillSpellSummary()
317{
318 UnitAI::FillAISpellInfo();
319
320 SpellSummary = new TSpellSummary[sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfoStoreSize()];
321
322 SpellInfo const* pTempSpell;
323
324 for (uint32 i = 0; i < sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfoStoreSize(); ++i)
325 {
326 SpellSummary[i].Effects = 0;
327 SpellSummary[i].Targets = 0;
328
329 pTempSpell = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(i);
330 // This spell doesn't exist.
331 if (!pTempSpell)
332 continue;
333
334 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : pTempSpell->GetEffectsForDifficulty(DIFFICULTY_NONE))
335 {
336 if (!effect)
337 continue;
338
339 // Spell targets self.
340 if (effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_CASTER)
341 SpellSummary[i].Targets |= 1 << (SELECT_TARGET_SELF-1);
342
343 // Spell targets a single enemy.
344 if (effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_TARGET_ENEMY ||
345 effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_TARGET_ENEMY)
346 SpellSummary[i].Targets |= 1 << (SELECT_TARGET_SINGLE_ENEMY-1);
347
348 // Spell targets AoE at enemy.
349 if (effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_SRC_AREA_ENEMY ||
350 effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_DEST_AREA_ENEMY ||
351 effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_SRC_CASTER ||
352 effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_DYNOBJ_ENEMY)
353 SpellSummary[i].Targets |= 1 << (SELECT_TARGET_AOE_ENEMY-1);
354
355 // Spell targets an enemy.
356 if (effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_TARGET_ENEMY ||
357 effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_TARGET_ENEMY ||
358 effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_SRC_AREA_ENEMY ||
359 effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_DEST_AREA_ENEMY ||
360 effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_SRC_CASTER ||
361 effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_DYNOBJ_ENEMY)
362 SpellSummary[i].Targets |= 1 << (SELECT_TARGET_ANY_ENEMY-1);
363
364 // Spell targets a single friend (or self).
365 if (effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_CASTER ||
366 effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_TARGET_ALLY ||
367 effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_TARGET_PARTY)
368 SpellSummary[i].Targets |= 1 << (SELECT_TARGET_SINGLE_FRIEND-1);
369
370 // Spell targets AoE friends.
371 if (effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_CASTER_AREA_PARTY ||
372 effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_LASTTARGET_AREA_PARTY ||
373 effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_SRC_CASTER)
374 SpellSummary[i].Targets |= 1 << (SELECT_TARGET_AOE_FRIEND-1);
375
376 // Spell targets any friend (or self).
377 if (effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_CASTER ||
378 effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_TARGET_ALLY ||
379 effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_TARGET_PARTY ||
380 effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_CASTER_AREA_PARTY ||
381 effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_LASTTARGET_AREA_PARTY ||
382 effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_SRC_CASTER)
383 SpellSummary[i].Targets |= 1 << (SELECT_TARGET_ANY_FRIEND-1);
384
385 // Make sure that this spell includes a damage effect.
386 if (effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_SCHOOL_DAMAGE ||
387 effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_INSTAKILL ||
388 effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_ENVIRONMENTAL_DAMAGE ||
389 effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_HEALTH_LEECH)
390 SpellSummary[i].Effects |= 1 << (SELECT_EFFECT_DAMAGE-1);
391
392 // Make sure that this spell includes a healing effect (or an apply aura with a periodic heal).
393 if (effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL ||
394 effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL_MAX_HEALTH ||
395 effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL_MECHANICAL ||
396 (effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA && effect->ApplyAuraName == 8))
397 SpellSummary[i].Effects |= 1 << (SELECT_EFFECT_HEALING-1);
398
399 // Make sure that this spell applies an aura.
400 if (effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA)
401 SpellSummary[i].Effects |= 1 << (SELECT_EFFECT_AURA-1);
402 }
403 }
404}

406void ScriptMgr::CreateSpellScripts(uint32 spellId, std::list<SpellScript*>& scriptVector)
407{
408 SpellScriptsBounds bounds = sObjectMgr->GetSpellScriptsBounds(spellId);
409
410 for (SpellScriptsContainer::iterator itr = bounds.first; itr != bounds.second; ++itr)
411 {
412 SpellScriptLoader* tmpscript = ScriptRegistry<SpellScriptLoader>::GetScriptById(itr->second);
413 if (!tmpscript)
414 continue;
415
416 SpellScript* script = tmpscript->GetSpellScript();
417
418 if (!script)
419 continue;
420
421 script->_Init(&tmpscript->GetName(), spellId);
422
423 scriptVector.push_back(script);
424 }
425}
426
427void ScriptMgr::CreateAuraScripts(uint32 spellId, std::list<AuraScript*>& scriptVector)
428{
429 SpellScriptsBounds bounds = sObjectMgr->GetSpellScriptsBounds(spellId);
430
431 for (SpellScriptsContainer::iterator itr = bounds.first; itr != bounds.second; ++itr)
432 {
433 SpellScriptLoader* tmpscript = ScriptRegistry<SpellScriptLoader>::GetScriptById(itr->second);
434 if (!tmpscript)
435 continue;
436
437 AuraScript* script = tmpscript->GetAuraScript();
438
439 if (!script)
440 continue;
441
442 script->_Init(&tmpscript->GetName(), spellId);
443
444 scriptVector.push_back(script);
445 }
446}
447
448void ScriptMgr::CreateSpellScriptLoaders(uint32 spellId, std::vector<std::pair<SpellScriptLoader*, SpellScriptsContainer::iterator> >& scriptVector)
449{
450 SpellScriptsBounds bounds = sObjectMgr->GetSpellScriptsBounds(spellId);
451 scriptVector.reserve(std::distance(bounds.first, bounds.second));
452
453 for (SpellScriptsContainer::iterator itr = bounds.first; itr != bounds.second; ++itr)
454 {
455 SpellScriptLoader* tmpscript = ScriptRegistry<SpellScriptLoader>::GetScriptById(itr->second);
456 if (!tmpscript)
457 continue;
458
459 scriptVector.push_back(std::make_pair(tmpscript, itr));
460 }
461}

586#define SCR_MAP_BGN(M, V, I, E, C, T) \
587 if (V->GetEntry() && V->GetEntry()->T()) \
588 { \
589 FOR_SCRIPTS(M, I, E) \
590 { \
591 MapEntry const* C = I->second->GetEntry(); \
592 if (!C) \
593 continue; \
594 if (C->ID == V->GetId()) \
595 {
596
597#define SCR_MAP_END \
598 return; \
599 } \
600 } \
601 }

603void ScriptMgr::OnCreateMap(Map* map)
604{
605 ASSERT(map);
606
607 SCR_MAP_BGN(WorldMapScript, map, itr, end, entry, IsWorldMap);
608 itr->second->OnCreate(map);
609 SCR_MAP_END;
610
611 SCR_MAP_BGN(InstanceMapScript, map, itr, end, entry, IsDungeon);
612 itr->second->OnCreate((InstanceMap*)map);
613 SCR_MAP_END;
614
615 SCR_MAP_BGN(BattlegroundMapScript, map, itr, end, entry, IsBattleground);
616 itr->second->OnCreate((BattlegroundMap*)map);
617 SCR_MAP_END;
618}

1025std::vector<ChatCommand> ScriptMgr::GetChatCommands()
1026{
1027 std::vector<ChatCommand> table;
1028
1029 FOR_SCRIPTS_RET(CommandScript, itr, end, table)
1030 {
1031 std::vector<ChatCommand> cmds = itr->second->GetCommands();
1032 table.insert(table.end(), cmds.begin(), cmds.end());
1033 }
1034
1035 // Sort commands in alphabetical order
1036 std::sort(table.begin(), table.end(), [](const ChatCommand& a, const ChatCommand&b)
1037 {
1038 return strcmp(a.Name, b.Name) < 0;
1039 });
1040
1041 return table;
1042}
